Data Literacy
Data Repository - A general term referring to data that has been collected, organized, and isolated. Databases, Data Warehouses, Big Data Stores
Databases - allowing storing data and querying to retrieve data. Relational Databases RDBMS have structured data in flat files. NoSQL are non-relational databases such as social media data built for speed. Querying data gives an advantage because it allows one to retrieve millions or records in seconds. 
IBM DB2
Microsoft SQL Server
MySQL
Oracle Database
PostgreSQL
Data Warehouse - Consolidates data from different sources through the extract, transform, and load process (ETL). 
Big Data Stores - Allow storage for Big Data
No-SQL - Not Only SQL data
Key-value store
Document based
MongoDB, DocumentDB, CouchDB, Cloudant are document based databases
Column based
Cassandra, Apache HBase
Graph based
Neo4J, CosmosDB
Best for social networks, fraud detection, product recommendations, access management, and network diagrams because it shows graphs interconnected with other similar data. Low cost shema-agnostic, similar design
Data Warehouse
A multipurpose enabler of operational and performance analytics. First data comes from the source, the ETL pipeline and then stored in the data warehouse to provide report ready data. 
Data Mart
A subsection of a data warehouse for a community of users or particular function. Such as Sales or Finance being given quarterly projections
Data Lake
Raw, unprocessed data with metadata and tags 
Extract, Transform, Load Process
Cleaning, standardizing and transforming data into usable format.
Data Pipeline
The entire journey of moving data from one system to another, including the ETL process. Can be used for both batch and streaming data. Apache Beam is for data pipelines. 
