These are the most popular languages for Data Science, however there are unique use cases for the following languages:
JavaScript, PHP, Go, Ruby, Visual Basic
R language’s array-oriented syntax makes it easier to translate from math to code for learners with no or minimal programming background. 
C++
C++ is a general purpose language that enables system programming to improve processing speed and gives broader control over the application. Applications built with C++ are TensorFlow, a Deep Learning library, MongoDB, a NoSQL database for data management, and Caffe, a deep learning algorithm repository. 
JavaScript
General purpose language that extended beyond the browser with Node.js
Julia
Designed for high-performance numerical analysis and computational science
